[2]
Date: Fri 20 Sep 2002
From: Judi Galeota <jgaleota@biocomp.unl.edu>

Further information from Nebraska
---------------------------------
Both of these animals [see: West Nile virus, caprine & ovine - USA
(Nebraska) 20020914.5306] tested positive by IHC in the brain, as well as by
PCR on brain tissue. The National Veterinary Services Laboratory (NVSL) in
Ames IA confirmed our PCR findings and isolated virus from brain tissue of
both animals as well. They also confirmed an serum neutralization titer of >
1:100 in the ovine serum.
Unfortunately, after our initial posting, all further discussion has taken
place on the American Association of Veterinary Laboratory Diagnosticians
(AAVLD) list serve. Sorry for the lack of follow-up. Here in Nebraska we are
so buried in West Nile virus cases that these kind of follow-ups have
slipped through the cracks. We have also observed 2 squirrels with positive
IHC staining in the brain as well as positive PCRs.
--
Judith A. Galeota
Veterinary Diagnostic Center
University of Nebraska
Lincoln, NE 68583
<jgaleota@biocomp.unl.edu>

